  "response_text": "# Healthy Indian-Spiced Chicken Breast\n\n## Simple Dry Rub Method\n\n**Spices to use:**\n- 1 tsp cumin powder\n- 1 tsp coriander powder\n- ½ tsp turmeric\n- ½ tsp garam masala\n- ¼ tsp black pepper\n- ¼ tsp chili powder (adjust to taste)\n- Salt to taste\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. **Mix the spices** in a small bowl\n2. **Pat the chicken dry** with paper towels\n3. **Rub the spice mixture** evenly on both sides\n4. **Cook using a healthy method:**\n   - Grill or bake at 400°F (200°C) for 20-25 minutes\n   - Air fry for 15-18 minutes\n   - Pan-sear in minimal oil, then finish in the oven\n\n## Optional Yogurt Marinade (More Traditional)\n\nMix spices with:\n- ½ cup plain Greek yogurt\n- 1 tbsp lemon juice\n- 1 tsp ginger-garlic paste\n\nMarinate for 30 minutes before cooking.\n\n## Benefits\n\n✓ No added sugar or excess salt\n✓ Anti-inflammatory spices\n✓ Rich in antioxidants\n✓ Authentic flavor without heavy cream or oil\n\nThis method keeps the chicken lean while delivering authentic Indian flavors!",
